CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 17, 1954, pg. 13, reads: "Back Liberian Maternity Clinic - This group of ladies, representing several church denominations, are an inspired and dedicated group who plan to work to set up and equip a maternity mission clinic in Monrovia, Liberia. Urged on by Mrs. Louise Nalls, who organized them after hearing Mrs. Margaret Johnson lecture on the missionary work she had begun there nine years before, the group also had the pleasure of hearing the missionary, recently.  Persons interested in contributing to the work are asked to call COurt 1-5930.  Shown in picture are Mrs. Dovie Rae Jeter, Mrs. Eula Robinson, Mrs. Margaret Johnson (the missionary), Lorraine Hamilton, Inez Wilds, Mattie Davis, Rubye Meadows, Bessie Powell, Ella M. Ruffin, Geneva D. Giles, Louise Nalls, Effie Garner, Rachel Washington and Mary Richards. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of women planning maternity clinic in Liberia, including Dovie Rae Jeter, Eula Robinson, Margaret Johnson, Lorraine Hamilton, Inez Wilds, Mattie Davis, Rubye Meadows, Bessie Powell, Ella M. Ruffin, Geneva D. Giles, Louise Nalls, Effie Garner, Rachel Washington, and Mary Richards, posed in living room, another version
